#: src/users/platform_overview/atari.md:3
msgid ""
"In some cases, the devices FujiNet provides are meant to simulate real Atari "
"peripherals, such as floppy disk drives (`D:` devices), RS232 and modem "
"interfaces (`R:` devices), and more."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/platform_overview/atari.md:5
msgid ""
"Utilizing the device's Wi-Fi networking capabilities, it's possible to "
"connect to other devices on a local network or Internet, e.g. [Bulletin "
"Board Systems (BBSes)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bulletin_board_system) "
"or other systems over Telnet, or even mounting floppy disk images from the "
"\"cloud\"."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/platform_overview/atari.md:11
msgid "C:<br>(Cassette)"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/platform_overview/atari.md:11
msgid "Prototype Working"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/platform_overview/atari.md:11
msgid ""
"Load a CAS image (FUJI format) from MicroSD named test.cas. Write CAS file "
"to MicroSD. Use browser to set PLAY or RECORD state. Short-press Button B to "
"enable the C: device. Install a 10-kohm pulldown resistor on the MOTOR line."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/platform_overview/atari.md:12
msgid "D:<br>(Disk)"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/platform_overview/atari.md:12
#: src/users/platform_overview/atari.md:15
#: src/users/platform_overview/atari.md:16
msgid "Working"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/platform_overview/atari.md:12
msgid ""
"Load floppy disk images from onboard MicroSD or networked TNFS server. "
"Currently supports ATR and XEX. ATX in progress"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/platform_overview/atari.md:13
msgid "N:<br>(Network)"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/platform_overview/atari.md:13
msgid "Working / In Progress"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/platform_overview/atari.md:13
msgid ""
"NEW networking device. FujiNet configuration commands in place and working "
"(WiFi, mounting, etc). TCP/UDP working. Handler in progress."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/platform_overview/atari.md:14
#: src/hardware/official_versions.md:104
msgid "Other"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/platform_overview/atari.md:14
msgid ""
"SIO2BT Bluetooth Connection. Apetime Real Time Clock (NTP). SAM Text To "
"Speech as a printer, voice output from #FujiNet to Atari. MIDIMaze network "
"gaming."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/platform_overview/atari.md:15
msgid "P:<br>(Printer)"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/platform_overview/atari.md:15
msgid ""
"Printer output saved to PDF files downloadable from the device. Available "
"Printers: 820, 822, 825, 1020, 1025, 1027, 1029, Espon 80, Okimate 10, HTML "
"for copy/paste, GRANTIC Screen Printer."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/platform_overview/atari.md:16
msgid "R:<br>(Modem)"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/platform_overview/atari.md:16
msgid ""
"850 Modem emulation, supports Type 1 Poll to load handler. Works with "
"existing communications programs such as Ice-T, BobTerm, AMODEM, PLATOTERM, "
"and BBS servers."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/platform_overview/atari.md:18
msgid ""
"Since devices are handled via the Atari OS's Central I/O (CIO) subsystem, "
"practically any programming language on the Atari will be able to make use "
"of these network features. For example, here's a simple networked program in "
"BASIC:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/platform_overview/atari.md:20
msgid ""
"```basic\n"
"10 OPEN #1,12,0,\"N:HTTP://WWW.GOOGLE.COM/\"\n"
"20 DIM A$(1024):TRAP 100\n"
"30 INPUT #1,A$:PRINT A$:GOTO 30\n"
"100 CLOSE #1\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/platform_overview/atari.md:26
msgid ""
"On top of TLS and UDP, cryptographic protocols designed to provide "
"communications security over computer networks, [Transport Layer Security "
"(TLS)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transport_Layer_Security) and [Datagram "
"Transport Layer Security "
"(DTLS)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Datagram_Transport_Layer_Security) "
"respectively, are also a possibility, thanks to the computing horsepower of "
"device powering FujiNet."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/platform_overview/atari.md:28
msgid "More information"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/platform_overview/atari.md:29
msgid ""
