#: src/users/quickstart/atari.md:50 src/users/quickstart/adam.md:52
msgid "Connecting Your FujiNet"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/atari.md:52
msgid "Follow these steps to connect FujiNet to your Atari for the first time:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/atari.md:64
msgid "Start with your Atari computer and FujiNet both **powered off**."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/atari.md:65
msgid "Remove any cartridges from your Atari's cartridge slot."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/atari.md:66
msgid ""
"Remove any SIO cable or device currently connected to your Atari's SIO "
"peripheral port."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/atari.md:67
msgid "Plug the FujiNet firmly into your Atari's SIO peripheral port."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/atari.md:68
msgid ""
"For now, do not plug anything into the FujiNet's SIO receptacle (back port)."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/atari.md:69
msgid "Optionally, provide power to the FujiNet via a USB cable."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/atari.md:70
msgid "Make sure the FujiNet's power switch is in the \"On\" position (up)."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/atari.md:72
msgid ""
"**Note -- Atari 400/800 Users:** The Atari 400/800 (or XL/XE systems running "
"the 800 OS) currently require external USB power for FujiNet, because "
"FujiNet does not come online fast enough from SIO bus power alone. A "
"workaround: power on the 800 while holding **Start** (to attempt a cassette "
"boot), wait for FujiNet to fully power up, then press **Reset** to reboot "
"into CONFIG."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/atari.md:74
msgid ""
"**Note -- Persistent Mounts:** If you connect external USB power to your "
"FujiNet, it will keep settings active (such as mounted disks) even when the "
"Atari is powered off. This is useful if you need to keep disks mounted "
"between boots."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/atari.md:78
msgid "Boot Up and Connect to WiFi"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/atari.md:80
msgid "Turn on your Atari computer."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/atari.md:81
msgid ""
"FujiNet will begin responding as disk drive #1. The rightmost (orange) LED "
"will blink, and you should hear SIO activity beeping from your TV or monitor "
"speaker."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/atari.md:82
msgid "The **FujiNet CONFIG** program will appear on screen."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/atari.md:83
msgid ""
"Choose your WiFi network from the list, or select `<Enter a specific SSID>` "
"to type it manually. Press **Esc** to rescan for networks."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/atari.md:84
msgid "Enter your WiFi network password, if required."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/atari.md:85
msgid ""
"If the password is correct, you will see the \"Connected to Network\" "
"confirmation screen."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/atari.md:86
msgid ""
"Once connected, the Host and Slot screen will appear, and you are ready to "
"mount disk images."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/atari.md:88
msgid ""
"**Important:** FujiNet uses the Espressif ESP32 chipset, which operates on "
"**2.4 GHz WiFi only**. If you use a dual-band (2.4/5 GHz) router with a "
"shared SSID, you may experience connectivity issues. Symptoms include "
"inability to ping the FujiNet, connect to TNFS servers, or reach the web "
"interface. Consider setting up a dedicated 2.4 GHz SSID if problems arise."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/atari.md:92
msgid "How Booting Works"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/atari.md:94
msgid ""
"When you turn on (or reboot) your Atari, it searches for devices on the SIO "
"bus. Any device responding as \"disk drive #1\" (`D1:`) will be used for "
"booting -- whether that is a real floppy drive, a virtual drive (SIO2SD, "
"SDriveMax), or FujiNet."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/atari.md:96
msgid ""
"When FujiNet is connected and powered on, if **no other device** responds as "
"`D1:` after a moment, FujiNet will respond. It will either boot the disk "
"image mounted in its drive slot 1, or load the CONFIG program."
msgstr ""

