#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:3
msgid "FujiApple: the Apple II & III FujiNet"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:5
msgid ""
"The \"production ready\" version of the FujiApple, Rev1, was released in "
"June 2023. A SmartPort-enabled Apple II/III is required for most functions "
"(see below for expansion card combinations that provide SmartPort "
"functionality for non-SmartPort-native Apples)."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:7
msgid "FujiNet emulates the following devices:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:9
msgid "**SmartPort drives** (HDV, PO, 2MG)"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:10
msgid "**Disk II** (WOZ, PO \\[140K\\], DSK)"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:11
msgid "**CP/M** (via [RunCPM](https://github.com/MockbaTheBorg/RunCPM))"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:12
msgid "**Clock**"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:13
msgid "**Modem**"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:14
#: src/developers/programming/adam/overview.md:13
msgid "**Printer**"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:16
msgid ""
"The clock, modem, and printer are presented as SmartPort devices, and "
"therefore require software or ROM support (for example, printer support is "
"available via a custom Apple IIc ROM on that model)."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:18
msgid ""
"CP/M support is provided through a fully emulated RunCPM environment with "
"storage on the built-in microSD slot."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:20
msgid ""
"**Important:** Rev0 and Rev00 do not support CP/M without a hardware "
"modification to the board, but all other functions are supported."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:26
msgid ""
"**Power:** FujiNet draws power from the SmartPort cable and powers on when "
"the Apple is turned on. There is no separate power switch."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:27
msgid ""
"**MicroSD slot:** Push/push MicroSD slot. An SD card is not required for "
"use. The SD card must be formatted **FAT32**; exFAT is not supported."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:28
msgid ""
"**Status LEDs:** White LED indicates WiFi connection; amber/yellow LED "
"indicates bus activity (SmartPort/Disk II)."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:29
msgid "**Buttons:** Button A (function to be determined) and Reset."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:30
msgid ""
"**Port:** One IDC20 port for SmartPort/Disk II connections, using a suitable "
"cable or adapter for your interface/controller."
msgstr ""

