#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:201
msgid "Two options are available to connect the FujiNet:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:203
msgid ""
"**Liron card** -- Allows SmartPort drives only. Requires a DB19 to 20-pin "
"adapter to connect the FujiNet to the Liron card."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:204
msgid ""
"**SoftSP card or DIY SoftSP on Grappler+** -- FujiNet is connected to either "
"the external or internal drive port with a 26-pin to 20-pin adapter cable."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:206
msgid ""
"The driver and some prebuilt 16MB SOS images are available here: [Apple III "
"FujiNet "
"Driver](https://github.com/FujiNetWIFI/fujinet-apps/tree/master/drivers/apple3)"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:213
msgid ""
"The first time you boot FujiNet CONFIG, it will prompt you to connect to "
"WiFi. Select your access point and enter its passphrase. This information is "
"saved internally and, if an SD card is present, is also saved to "
"[fnconfig.ini](https://github.com/FujiNetWIFI/fujinet-platformio/wiki/FujiNet-Configuration-File%3A-fnconfig.ini)."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:215
msgid ""
"**Important:** FujiNet is powered by the Espressif ESP32 chipset, which "
"works on **2.4 GHz WiFi networks only**. If you are using a \"mixed\" 2.4 "
"GHz / 5 GHz WiFi network (both radio bands with the same SSID/network name), "
"you **may** have problems connecting your FujiNet device to the network."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:217 src/users/quickstart/adam.md:109
msgid "Main Screen Layout"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:219
msgid ""
"The CONFIG screen shows **host slots** on the top and **disk slots** on the "
"bottom. Press `Tab` to jump between the host slots and disk slots. Press "
"`Return` on a highlighted host slot to begin selecting and mounting a disk "
"image from that host to an emulated disk drive."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:221
msgid "Host Types"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:223
msgid "Hosts can be:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:225
msgid ""
"An IP address or hostname of a **TNFS server** (for example: "
"`apps.irata.online`, `fujinet.diller.org`, `tnfs.fujinet.online`, "
"`10.0.27.222`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:226
msgid ""
"An **SMB** or **FTP** server URL in the form `SMB://server.address` or "
"`FTP://server.address` -- both require anonymous access; `server.address` "
"can be an IP address or domain name"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:227
msgid "**`SD`** -- points to the onboard SD card socket"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:229
msgid "Editing Hosts"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:231
msgid ""
"With a host entry selected, press `E` to edit it. Host entries can be up to "
"30 characters long."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:235
msgid "Select the desired host and then a disk image file."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:236
msgid ""
"When prompted, select a disk drive. The first four drives are SmartPort "
"devices; the last two are Disk II Drive 1 and Drive 2."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:237
msgid ""
"Choose to mount it **Read Only** (press `R` or `Return`) or **Read/Write** "
"(press `W`)."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:239
msgid ""
"**Caution:** Most if not all public-facing TNFS servers do not allow write "
"access, so you should mount them as read-only."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:241
msgid ""
"**Note:** Disk II emulation in FujiNet is read-only (as of August 2024), so "
"mount those disks accordingly."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:243
msgid "Booting"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:245
msgid ""
"When returned to the main CONFIG screen, press `Esc` to reset the Apple II. "
"For systems that need it, press `Ctrl`+`Reset` and type `PR#X` (where X is "
"the slot of your DIY SoftSP ROM card, or the slot of the physical drive "
"interface card to boot from the Disk II emulated drive)."
msgstr ""

