#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:287
msgid "Apple Disk Types, Filesystems, and Slots"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:289
msgid ""
"This section provides technical background on Apple II disk image formats "
"and how they relate to FujiNet's drive emulation."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:291
msgid "The Relationship Between Sector Order and Filesystem"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:293
msgid "The FujiNet codebase currently categorizes disk images by sector order:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:295
msgid "`MEDIATYPE_DO` -- DOS 3.3 sector order"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:296
msgid "`MEDIATYPE_DSK` -- Ambiguous (could be either order)"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:297
msgid "`MEDIATYPE_PO` -- ProDOS sector order"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:298
msgid "`MEDIATYPE_WOZ` -- WOZ format"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:300
msgid ""
"However, what actually determines where a disk image can be mounted (Disk II "
"vs. SmartPort) is the **filesystem**, not the sector order. The sector order "
"can always be corrected on the fly."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:302
msgid "Proposed Media Type Model"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:304
msgid ""
"A more correct model would distinguish between filesystem presence and "
"sector order:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:306
msgid "Media Type"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:306
msgid "Mountable As"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:308
msgid "`MEDIATYPE_WOZ`"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:308
msgid "WOZ format"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:308 src/users/quickstart/apple.md:309
#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:311
msgid "Disk II"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:309
msgid "`MEDIATYPE_DO`"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:309
msgid ".DSK or .DO 140K, DOS 3.3 sector order, no ProDOS filesystem"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:310
msgid "`MEDIATYPE_DO_PF`"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:310
msgid ".DSK or .DO 140K, DOS 3.3 sector order, ProDOS filesystem"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:310 src/users/quickstart/apple.md:312
msgid "Disk II or SmartPort"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:311
msgid "`MEDIATYPE_PO`"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:311
msgid ".DSK or .PO 140K, ProDOS sector order, no ProDOS filesystem"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:312
msgid "`MEDIATYPE_PO_PF`"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:312
msgid ".DSK or .PO 140K, ProDOS sector order, ProDOS filesystem"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:313
msgid "`MEDIATYPE_HDV`"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:313
msgid ".PO or .HDV >140K, ProDOS sector order, ProDOS filesystem"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:315
msgid ""
"The key insight is that SmartPort can only mount images with a ProDOS "
"filesystem, while Disk II can mount any 140K image regardless of filesystem."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:317
msgid "Apple II Slots and FujiNet Drive Slots"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:319
msgid "Historical Background"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:321
msgid ""
"The original Apple II has 8 slots (0-7). Slot 0 is limited and slot 7 is "
"extended. The conventional arrangement that developed over time:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:323
msgid "**Slots 1-2:** Character I/O (printers, serial/modems)"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:324
msgid "**Slot 6:** Disk II (became a de-facto standard)"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:325
msgid ""
"**Slot 7:** SmartPort (allows quick autoboot for daily use while still "
"permitting `PR#6` to boot software that expects Disk II in slot 6)"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:327
msgid ""
"The autostart ROM searches for a bootable device starting from slot 7 and "
"working downward. SmartPort can quickly determine if a bootable drive is "
"connected, while the Disk II requires a long time to determine that no disk "
"is present."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:329
msgid "What This Means for FujiNet"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:331
msgid ""
"FujiNet cannot know or presume any slot location of the Disk II card or "
"SmartPort card in the Apple II. The only meaningful terminology for FujiNet "
"users is:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:334 src/users/quickstart/apple.md:337
msgid "Drive 1"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:335 src/users/quickstart/apple.md:338
msgid "Drive 2"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:339
msgid "Drive 3"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:340
msgid "Drive 4"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:342
msgid "Yellowstone SmartPort and Disk II Modes"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:344
msgid ""
"The Yellowstone is a single firmware in a single expansion slot, unlike the "
"Disk II + SoftSP combination which occupies two slots. Key considerations:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:346
msgid ""
"In SmartPort mode, Yellowstone handles Disk II internally and presents Disk "
"II drives as 140K SmartPort devices to ProDOS. This differs from native Disk "
"II handling (for example, ProDOS 2.5's improved Disk II support is not "
"available through Yellowstone without a firmware update)."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:347
msgid ""
"Switching between ProDOS and DOS 3.3 requires switching Yellowstone between "
"SmartPort mode and Disk II mode."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:349
msgid "Number of SmartPort Drives"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/apple.md:351
msgid ""
"ProDOS 8 has a strict limit of **2 drives per slot**. To leverage additional "
"SmartPort drives, ProDOS 8 remaps them to phantom slots. This process is "
"limited to one phantom slot, so ProDOS 8 supports a maximum of **4 SmartPort "
"drives**. GS/OS does not have this limitation and may support more SmartPort "
"drives."
msgstr ""

