#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:1
msgid "Commodore 64 Quickstart Guide"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:3
msgid ""
"Welcome to the FujiNet quickstart guide for the Commodore 64. FujiNet for "
"Commodore (also known as \"Meatloaf\" / \"Fujiloaf\") connects via the IEC "
"bus and provides network access, file loading, and more. For a broader "
"overview of all supported platforms, see the [Platform "
"Overview](../platform_overview.md)."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:5
msgid ""
"**Beta Notice:** FujiNet for Commodore is currently in active development. "
"Software and hardware features are subject to change. Join the [FujiNet "
"Discord](https://discord.gg/7MfFTvD) for the latest updates."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:9
msgid "Hardware Options"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:11
msgid ""
"FujiNet for Commodore uses the IEC bus, making prototype construction "
"relatively straightforward -- just 6 wires and an ESP32. Several hardware "
"options are available:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:13
msgid "Custom Prototype"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:15
msgid "You need:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:16
msgid ""
"An **ESP32-WROVER DevKit** board (minimum 8 MB Flash, 8 MB PSRAM) -- the "
"official **ESP32-DEVKITC-VE** from Espressif is recommended"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:17
msgid "A **DIN 6 plug** (for the IEC bus connection)"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:18
msgid "Wire to connect them"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:20
msgid ""
"Use the pinout defined in the [generic IEC board "
"configuration](https://github.com/FujiNetWIFI/fujinet-platformio/blob/master/include/pinmap/iec.h#L44)."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:22
msgid "LOLIN D32 Pro"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:24
msgid ""
"The LOLIN D32 Pro ESP32 board includes an onboard Micro-SD card socket and "
"additional hardware that may be enabled in future firmware versions. It is "
"available from AliExpress."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:26
msgid "Load the **Meatloaf-Specialty** firmware for this board"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:27
msgid ""
"See the [FujiNet firmware "
"wiki](https://github.com/FujiNetWIFI/fujinet-platformio/wiki) for wiring "
"details"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:29
msgid "FujiApple Adapter"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:31
msgid ""
"If you have a FujiApple Rev0 (FujiNet for Apple II), you can repurpose it "
"for Commodore testing by building an IEC-to-FujiApple adapter cable."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:33
msgid "When configuring the firmware build, set: `build_board = fujiapple-iec`"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:37
msgid "Firmware Installation"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:39
msgid ""
"Follow the [Board Bring Up "
"Guide](https://github.com/FujiNetWIFI/fujinet-platformio/wiki/Board-Bring-Up-Software) "
"to install PlatformIO and build the Commodore firmware."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:43
msgid "Setting Up WiFi"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:45
msgid ""
"Since there is not yet a fully working on-screen CONFIG for the Commodore, "
"you have two options to configure WiFi:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:47
msgid "Option 1: Edit the SD Card Directly"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:49
msgid ""
"Remove the SD card from FujiNet, insert it into your computer, and create or "
"edit the `fnconfig.ini` file with your WiFi credentials."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:51
msgid "Option 2: Set WiFi from BASIC"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:53
msgid "Start your Commodore 64 with FujiNet attached to the IEC bus."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:54
msgid ""
"Switch to upper/lowercase mode by pressing the **Commodore key** + **Shift**."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:55
msgid "Enter the following command, substituting your network name and password:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:57
msgid ""
"```\n"
"OPEN1,15,15,\"SETSSID:YourSSID,YourPassword\":CLOSE1\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:61
msgid "Reboot FujiNet. It should connect to your WiFi network."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:63
msgid ""
"**Tip:** If your SSID contains capital letters, the `SETSSID` command must "
"include those capitals. They may display as PETSCII characters on screen, "
"but will be sent correctly."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:67 src/users/quickstart/rs232.md:15
msgid "Connection Diagram"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:78
msgid "Using FujiNet as a Modem"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:80
msgid ""
"FujiNet can emulate a modem, letting you connect to BBSes and other telnet "
"services."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:82
msgid "NETCAT"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:84
msgid "Start your Commodore 64 with FujiNet attached."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:85
msgid "Load NETCAT:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:87
msgid ""
"```\n"
"LOAD\"ML:NETCAT\",8\n"
"RUN\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:92
msgid "In the NETCAT terminal, type a telnet address:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:94
msgid ""
"```\n"
"telnet://bbs.retroacademy.it:6510\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:98
msgid "PTERM"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:100
msgid ""
"PTERM is a more full-featured terminal application available from the "
"Meatloaf file repository:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:102
msgid ""
"```\n"
"LOAD\"ML:PTERM\",8\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

