msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:117
msgid "Loading via TNFS"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:119
msgid ""
"TNFS loading works the same as on other FujiNet-supported platforms. Use "
"device number **12**:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:121
msgid ""
"```\n"
"LOAD\"TNFS://APPS.IRATA.ONLINE/PETSCIITERM.PRG\",12\n"
"RUN\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:126
msgid "More examples:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:128
msgid ""
"```\n"
"LOAD\"TNFS://FUJINET.DILLER.ORG/C64/DIGDUG.PRG\",12\n"
"RUN\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:133
msgid ""
"**Warning:** Due to PETSCII character mapping, always **type in uppercase** "
"on the Commodore. The URIs will be converted to lowercase when sent to "
"remote servers. Even if examples here appear in lowercase, type them in "
"uppercase on your Commodore."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:135
msgid "Loading via Meatloaf"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:137
msgid "Use the `ML:` prefix with device number **8**:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:139
msgid ""
"```\n"
"LOAD\"ML:GAME$\",8\n"
"LOAD\"ML:EMPIRE\",8,1\n"
"LOAD\"ML:DIGDUG\",8,1\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:145
msgid "Custom File Browser (FB64)"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:147
msgid ""
"The Meatloaf distribution includes a modified version of FB64, a file "
"browser for the Commodore 64/128. It supports navigation and loading of "
"files from both the local SD card and internet-connected Meatloaf file "
"repositories."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:149
msgid ""
"```\n"
"LOAD\"ML:FB64\",8\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:155
msgid "Advanced Features"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:157
msgid "JSON Parsing"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:159
msgid ""
"Meatloaf supports parsing JSON data from web APIs, opening up possibilities "
"for retrieving and displaying internet data on your Commodore. Here is an "
"example that fetches and displays a random joke from an API:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:161
msgid ""
"```basic\n"
"10 REM *** OPEN COMMS\n"
"11 OPEN 15,16,15, \"\"\n"
"12 OPEN 2,16,2,\"HTTPS://API.CHUCKNORRIS.IO/JOKES/RANDOM\"\n"
"20 REM *** RECEIVE, PARSE, PRINT DATA\n"
"21 PRINT#15, \"JSONPARSE,2\"\n"
"22 PRINT#15, \"JQ,2,/VALUE\"\n"
"23 PRINT#15, \"BITEPARSE,2,80\"\n"
"24 INPUT#2, J$: PRINT J$;\n"
"25 IF(ST AND 64)=0 THEN GOTO 24\n"
"30 REM *** CLOSE\n"
"31 CLOSE 2: CLOSE 15\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:175
msgid "Running Your Own File Server"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/quickstart/commodore.md:177
