#: src/users/n_device/overview.md:25
msgid ""
"The N: device acts as a bridge between your retro computer and the internet. "
"Your program issues standard I/O calls to the N: device, FujiNet translates "
"those into the appropriate network protocol operations, and the results are "
"passed back to your program."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/n_device/overview.md:27
msgid ""
"```mermaid\n"
"flowchart LR\n"
"    A[\"Retro Computer\n"
"    (Atari, Apple, etc.)\"] -->|\"CIO / SIO\n"
"    Commands\"| B[\"FujiNet\n"
"    N: Device Handler\"]\n"
"    B -->|\"TCP, UDP,\n"
"    HTTP, FTP, TNFS\"| C[\"Internet\n"
"    Services\"]\n"
"    C -->|\"Response\n"
"    Data\"| B\n"
"    B -->|\"Status &\n"
"    Data\"| A\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/n_device/overview.md:42
msgid "Data Flow in Detail"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/n_device/overview.md:44
msgid ""
"**Your program** issues a standard OPEN, READ, WRITE, or CLOSE call to the "
"N: device with a URL-like devicespec."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/n_device/overview.md:45
msgid ""
"**The N: device handler** (loaded into memory on your retro computer) "
"translates this into an SIO command and sends it to FujiNet."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/n_device/overview.md:46
msgid ""
"**FujiNet** parses the devicespec, determines the protocol, and performs the "
"actual network communication over WiFi."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/n_device/overview.md:47
msgid ""
"**Response data** flows back through FujiNet to the N: device handler and "
"into your program's I/O buffer."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/n_device/overview.md:49
msgid ""
"```mermaid\n"
"sequenceDiagram\n"
"    participant App as Your Program\n"
"    participant CIO as CIO Handler (NDEV)\n"
"    participant SIO as SIO Bus\n"
"    participant FN as FujiNet\n"
"    participant Net as Internet Host\n"
"\n"
"    App->>CIO: OPEN #1,4,0,\"N:HTTP://example.com/file.txt\"\n"
"    CIO->>SIO: Network Open ($4E)\n"
"    SIO->>FN: Devicespec buffer (256 bytes)\n"
"    FN->>Net: HTTP GET /file.txt\n"
"    Net-->>FN: Response data\n"
"    FN-->>SIO: ACK\n"
"    SIO-->>CIO: Success\n"
"    CIO-->>App: IOCB ready\n"
"\n"
"    App->>CIO: INPUT #1,A$\n"
"    CIO->>SIO: Network Read\n"
"    SIO->>FN: Read request\n"
"    FN-->>SIO: Data from buffer\n"
"    SIO-->>CIO: Data\n"
"    CIO-->>App: A$ = data\n"
"\n"
"    App->>CIO: CLOSE #1\n"
"    CIO->>SIO: Network Close\n"
"    SIO->>FN: Close connection\n"
"    FN-->>SIO: ACK\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

