"**UDP (User Datagram Protocol)** provides connectionless, datagram-oriented "
"communication. Unlike TCP, UDP does not guarantee delivery, ordering, or "
"duplicate protection. However, it is lightweight and efficient, making it "
"well suited for applications that send small, frequent updates to multiple "
"participants."
