#: src/users/n_device/basic_usage.md:1
msgid "BASIC Programming with the N: Device"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/n_device/basic_usage.md:3
msgid ""
"The N: device is a standard CIO device, which means it can be used directly "
"from Atari BASIC and other platform BASICs. Once the NDEV handler is loaded, "
"you can load and save programs, read and write data files, and open direct "
"connections to TCP and UDP sockets -- all from BASIC."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/n_device/basic_usage.md:7
msgid "Before using the N: device from BASIC, ensure:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/n_device/basic_usage.md:9
