"FujiNet emulates a Hayes-compatible modem, translating AT dial commands into "
"TCP connections. BBS software running on your Atari sees FujiNet as a "
"standard modem. Remote callers use `ATDT yourhost:port` from their own "
"FujiNet to connect."
