#: src/users/updating_firmware/fujinet_flasher.md:187
msgid "App and Code Signing the Macintosh Flasher"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/updating_firmware/fujinet_flasher.md:189
msgid ""
"In order to not have a modern Mac (OSX) refuse to allow you to run the "
"Flasher.app when you first download and run it- it should be code signed and "
"app notorized with Apple. This requires a paid apple Dev account."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/updating_firmware/fujinet_flasher.md:191
msgid ""
"Andy Diller has one and has signed the 10.5 release. Below are directions if "
"anyone in the future or present would like to sign their own build for some "
"reason. You would have already setup your Dev account, made a Team, created "
"an app and app password."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/updating_firmware/fujinet_flasher.md:193
msgid "Step 1"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/updating_firmware/fujinet_flasher.md:195
msgid ""
"Get the Build Flasher.zip from Mozzwald. This is aleady in the right "
"structure to sign and then zip back up. The commands below assume you have "
"taken the zip from Moz and simply unzipped it into it's own directory. "
"Remove the original zip file as you will creating a new one."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/updating_firmware/fujinet_flasher.md:197
msgid "Step 2"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/updating_firmware/fujinet_flasher.md:199
msgid ""
"Follow the below commands. They should make some sense if you know what you "
"are doing. If they do not make sense then ask a friend or use one that is "
"already signed."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/updating_firmware/fujinet_flasher.md:201
msgid "Commands"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/updating_firmware/fujinet_flasher.md:204
msgid "\"Developer ID Application: YOUR NAME (YOUR ID)\""
msgstr ""

#: src/users/updating_firmware/fujinet_flasher.md:205
msgid "\"/Users/sjobs/flasher-sign/15/FujiNet-Flasher.app\""
msgstr ""

#: src/users/updating_firmware/fujinet_flasher.md:207
msgid "\"$SIGN_ID\" \"$APP_PATH/Contents/MacOS/FujiNet-Flasher\""
msgstr ""

#: src/users/updating_firmware/fujinet_flasher.md:208
msgid "\"$SIGN_ID\" \"$APP_PATH\""
msgstr ""

#: src/users/updating_firmware/fujinet_flasher.md:209
msgid "\"$APP_PATH\""
msgstr ""

#: src/users/updating_firmware/fujinet_flasher.md:225
msgid ""
"You are done. You can take that new ZIP and it should install on other's "
"Mac's without requiring them to go into Pref/Security and \"Run Anyway\" "
"etc. etc. etc..."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/updating_firmware/nightly_firmware_builds.md:3
msgid ""
"Every night an [automated GitHub "
"Action](https://github.com/FujiNetWIFI/fujinet-firmware/blob/master/.github/workflows/nightly.yml) "
"is triggered to build the FujiNet Firmware for multiple platforms that are "
"in a working state currently.  If successful, the resulting firmware ZIP "
"file is attached to a permanent special GitHub Pre-Release called [Nightly "
"Builds](https://github.com/FujiNetWIFI/fujinet-firmware/releases/tag/nightly)."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/updating_firmware/nightly_firmware_builds.md:5
msgid ""
"If you wish to try the bleeding edge current state of the `fujinet-firmware` "
"code but don't have a build environment of your own then this is the place "
"to go!  Download the appropriate file to your local computer & use the "
"[Fujinet Flasher](https://fujinet.online/download/) tool to flash your "
"FujiNet device with this custom-built ZIP file."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/updating_firmware/nightly_firmware_builds.md:7
msgid "\\[!WARNING\\] There is NO guarantee that these builds work!!"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/updating_firmware/nightly_firmware_builds.md:10
msgid ""
"These builds are **NOT** official builds & are provided 100% **AS-IS** with "
"absolutely no guarantee that they will work.  Only use these builds if you "
"know what you are doing & are willing to troubleshoot any problems on your "
"own."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/updating_firmware/nightly_firmware_builds.md:12
msgid ""
"Of course reporting any bugs you run across would be greatly appreciated but "
"they should be accompanied by console logs & any other appropriate details "
"that might help in troubleshooting the issues.  Generally the [FujiNet "
"Discord](https://discord.gg/yKtS3fxU) is the best place to discuss any "
"issues you find in these builds."
msgstr ""

