#: src/developers/programming/atari/overview.md:34
msgid "Programming Approaches"
msgstr ""

#: src/developers/programming/atari/overview.md:36
msgid "Atari BASIC"
msgstr ""

#: src/developers/programming/atari/overview.md:38
msgid ""
"The most accessible way to use the FujiNet is through Atari BASIC using "
"`OPEN`, `PRINT#`, `INPUT#`, `GET#`, and `XIO` commands with the `N:` device. "
"The N: handler must be loaded first (it loads automatically when booting "
"from FujiNet CONFIG)."
msgstr ""

#: src/developers/programming/atari/overview.md:40
msgid "**Quick Start -- Reading a Mastodon Post:**"
msgstr ""

#: src/developers/programming/atari/overview.md:42
msgid ""
"```basic\n"
"0 DIM A$(256)\n"
"1 TRAP 91\n"
"2 POKE 756,204\n"
"10 OPEN "
"#1,12,0,\"N:HTTPS://OLDBYTES.SPACE/api/v1/timelines/public?limit=1\"\n"
"20 XIO 252,#1,12,1,\"N:\":REM SET CHANNEL MODE TO JSON\n"
"30 XIO ASC(\"P\"),#1,12,0,\"N:\":REM PARSE THE JSON\n"
"40 XIO ASC(\"Q\"),#1,12,3,\"N:/0/account/display_name\"\n"
"50 INPUT #1,A$:? A$\n"
"60 XIO ASC(\"Q\"),#1,12,3,\"N:/0/created_at\"\n"
"70 INPUT #1,A$:? A$\n"
"80 XIO ASC(\"Q\"),#1,12,3,\"N:/0/content\"\n"
"90 GET #1,A:? CHR$(A);:GOTO 90\n"
"91 CLOSE #1:? :?\n"
"100 POKE 18,0:POKE 19,0:POKE 20,0\n"
"110 IF PEEK(19)<30 THEN 110\n"
"120 GOTO 1\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/developers/programming/atari/overview.md:61
msgid ""
"This example opens an HTTPS connection, switches the channel to JSON mode, "
"parses the response, queries specific JSON fields, and prints the results."
msgstr ""

#: src/developers/programming/atari/overview.md:63
msgid "Assembly Language"
msgstr ""

#: src/developers/programming/atari/overview.md:65
msgid ""
"For maximum performance and control, programmers can issue SIO calls "
"directly from 6502 assembly. This bypasses CIO overhead and communicates "
"with FujiNet device IDs `$70`\\-`$78` at the bus level. The SIO command "
"frame specifies the device ID, command byte, auxiliary bytes, buffer "
"address, and transfer length."
msgstr ""

#: src/developers/programming/atari/overview.md:67
msgid "cc65 (C Cross-Compiler)"
msgstr ""

#: src/developers/programming/atari/overview.md:69
msgid ""
"The [cc65](https://cc65.github.io/cc65/) cross-compiler for 6502 targets "
"provides a practical middle ground. The "
"[fujinet-lib](https://github.com/FujiNetWIFI/fujinet-lib) project offers a C "
"library that wraps the SIO interface, making FujiNet programming accessible "
"from C while retaining good performance."
msgstr ""

