#: src/developers/programming/commodore/overview.md:3
msgid ""
"Programming the FujiNet on Commodore platforms uses the **IEC (IEEE-488 "
"derivative) bus**, the same serial bus used by disk drives, printers, and "
"other Commodore peripherals. The FujiNet exposes two logical device numbers "
"on this bus: a **command channel** for system operations and a **network "
"device** for protocol-based I/O."
msgstr ""

#: src/developers/programming/commodore/overview.md:5
msgid "Device Numbers"
msgstr ""

#: src/developers/programming/commodore/overview.md:9
msgid "**15**"
msgstr ""

#: src/developers/programming/commodore/overview.md:9
msgid ""
"FujiNet command channel -- system configuration, WiFi management, "
"host/device slot operations"
msgstr ""

#: src/developers/programming/commodore/overview.md:10
msgid "**16**"
msgstr ""

#: src/developers/programming/commodore/overview.md:10
msgid ""
"Network device -- protocol-based network I/O (HTTP, HTTPS, TCP, UDP, FTP, "
"TNFS, etc.)"
msgstr ""

#: src/developers/programming/commodore/overview.md:12
msgid ""
"Standard Commodore file I/O commands (`OPEN`, `PRINT#`, `INPUT#`, `GET#`, "
"`CLOSE`) are used to communicate with both devices."
msgstr ""

#: src/developers/programming/commodore/overview.md:14
msgid "Command Channel (Device 15)"
msgstr ""

#: src/developers/programming/commodore/overview.md:16
msgid ""
"The command channel accepts text-based payloads to configure and query the "
"FujiNet. The general pattern is:"
msgstr ""

#: src/developers/programming/commodore/overview.md:18
msgid ""
"```basic\n"
"OPEN 1,15,15,\"COMMAND\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/developers/programming/commodore/overview.md:22
msgid ""
"Where `COMMAND` is a text string such as `ADAPTERCONFIG`, `SCAN`, `GETSSID`, "
"etc. Responses are read back with `INPUT#` or `GET#`."
msgstr ""

#: src/developers/programming/commodore/overview.md:24
msgid "Adapter Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: src/developers/programming/commodore/overview.md:26
msgid "Text Variant"
msgstr ""

#: src/developers/programming/commodore/overview.md:28
msgid "**Payload:** `ADAPTERCONFIG`"
msgstr ""

#: src/developers/programming/commodore/overview.md:30
msgid ""
"**Response:** Eight lines of text containing SSID, Hostname, IP, Netmask, "
"Gateway, DNS, MAC, BSSID, and firmware version."
msgstr ""

#: src/developers/programming/commodore/overview.md:32
msgid ""
"```basic\n"
"10 PRINT CHR$(147)\n"
"20 OPEN 1,15,15,\"ADAPTERCONFIG\"\n"
"30 INPUT#1,S$:PRINT;\n"
"40 PRINT \"    SSID: \";S$\n"
"50 INPUT#1,H$:PRINT;\n"
"60 PRINT \"HOSTNAME: \";H$\n"
"70 INPUT#1,I$:PRINT;\n"
"80 PRINT \"      IP: \";I$\n"
"90 INPUT#1,N$:PRINT;\n"
"100 PRINT \" NETMASK: \";N$\n"
"110 INPUT#1,G$:PRINT;\n"
"120 PRINT \" GATEWAY: \";G$\n"
"130 INPUT#1,D$:PRINT;\n"
"140 PRINT \"     DNS: \";D$\n"
"150 INPUT#1,M$:PRINT;\n"
"160 PRINT \"     MAC: \";M$\n"
"170 INPUT#1,B$:PRINT;\n"
"180 PRINT \"   BSSID: \";B$\n"
"190 INPUT#1,V$:PRINT;\n"
"200 PRINT \"     VER: \";V$\n"
"210 CLOSE1\n"
"220 END\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

