#: src/internals/feps/fep_004.md:14
msgid "Motivation"
msgstr ""

#: src/internals/feps/fep_004.md:16
msgid ""
"As FujiNet expands beyond its original Atari and Apple implementations, "
"maintaining consistency and interoperability across platforms has become "
"increasingly difficult. Each platform currently implements the FujiNet "
"protocol in slightly different ways, often resulting in duplicated codebases "
"and redundant logic. When a bug is fixed or a feature is added on one "
"platform, the change rarely propagates automatically to others -- every "
"update must be manually ported, tested, and maintained separately."
msgstr ""

#: src/internals/feps/fep_004.md:18
msgid ""
"The core reason for this duplication lies in how packets are structured and "
"parsed. The existing protocol uses fixed headers and context-dependent "
"payloads, requiring each command handler to read its own data in a custom "
"way. This design forces per-platform command handling logic."
msgstr ""

#: src/internals/feps/fep_004.md:20
msgid "Universal FujiNet Architecture"
msgstr ""

#: src/internals/feps/fep_004.md:22
msgid ""
"With the move toward a universal FujiNet architecture (modeled on the RS-232 "
"version), future devices will use a **Raspberry Pi RP2040 or RP2350** as the "
"physical bus interface, with an **ESP32 or host computer** managing device "
"emulation and network communication. In this architecture, the bus interface "
"and device logic may run on different processors, making serialization and "
"deserialization efficiency critical."
msgstr ""

#: src/internals/feps/fep_004.md:31
msgid "Design Goals"
msgstr ""

#: src/internals/feps/fep_004.md:33
msgid ""
"By making packets **self-describing**, each packet indicates the sizes of "
"its fields so they can be fully decoded immediately upon receipt:"
msgstr ""

#: src/internals/feps/fep_004.md:35
msgid ""
"**Generic decoding** -- packets can be parsed into C/C++ structures "
"immediately upon receipt"
msgstr ""

#: src/internals/feps/fep_004.md:36
msgid ""
"**Modular command handling** -- common handling implemented once in a base "
"class, device-specific logic in subclasses"
msgstr ""

#: src/internals/feps/fep_004.md:37
msgid ""
"**Code reuse** -- shared parsing, debugging, and validation routines across "
"all platforms"
msgstr ""

#: src/internals/feps/fep_004.md:38
msgid ""
"**Protocol introspection** -- tools can decode packets without hardcoded "
"command definitions"
msgstr ""

#: src/internals/feps/fep_004.md:39
msgid ""
"**Forward compatibility** -- new fields or data types can be introduced "
"without breaking existing implementations"
msgstr ""

#: src/internals/feps/fep_004.md:40
msgid ""
"**Legacy compatibility** -- implementable on 6502, 8080, and other 8-bit "
"processors"
msgstr ""

